Henry Martin (21 December 1763 – 19 July 1839) was a Member of Parliament. He represented the constituency of Kinsale from 29 April 1806 to 27 June 1818.
Martin owned the estate village of Colston Bassett and was responsible for the building of several larger houses including the rectory.He died on 19 July 1839, aged seventy-five.
